<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2439c</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-07T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 7,
                                            1918, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5236. Red Cross here is willing to undertake providing warm clothing,
                                other than uniforms, for 70,000 Czecho-Slovak troops in Siberia.
                                Please ascertain, discreetly, whether French Government contemplates
                                any similar assistance which would render it unnecessary for Red
                                Cross to undertake full responsibility for clothing, other than
                                uniforms. Answer urgent.<note n="2" xml:id="d397fn2">Answered Oct.
                                    2, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_403">p.
                                        403</ref>.</note></p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_PFL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>